Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The widow of late Governor Danbaba Danfulani Suntai of Taraba State has married the cousin of former First Lady Turai Umaru Yar’Adua. The two love birds Saad Malami and Hauwa Suntai wedded at the national Mosque in Abuja. Born into a Muslim family from Shuwa Arab tribe in Borno State, Hauwa converted to Christianity when she married Mr. Suntai decades ago. Sources said Mr. Malami, believed to be in his thirties is Turai Yar’Adua’s cousin and the marriage received the blessings of the Yar’Adua family Hauwa’s late husband was involved in a plane crash in October 2012 and died on June 28, 2017, in Houston, Florida, in the United States. Mr. Malami married Hauwa, who is in her 50s, in a low key event held at the National Mosque, Abuja on Saturday.